{lang-eng}All hail the power of Jesus’ name!
Let angels prostrate fall;
Bring forth the royal diadem,
And crown Him Lord of all;
Bring forth the royal diadem,
And crown Him Lord of all.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}You chosen seed of Israel’s race,
You ransomed from the fall,
Hail Him who saves you by His grace,
And crown Him Lord of all;
Hail Him, who saves you by His grace,
And crown Him Lord of all.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Let every kindred, every tribe,
On this terrestrial ball,
To Him all majesty ascribe,
And crown Him Lord of all;
To Him all majesty ascribe,
And crown Him Lord of all.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Oh, that with yonder sacred throng,
We at His feet may fall!
We’ll join the everlasting song,
And crown Him Lord of all;
We’ll join the everlasting song,
And crown Him Lord of all.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}All hail Him who is Christ our Lord;
In triumph let us call
Upon His name in one accord,
For He’s our all in all;
Upon His name in one accord,
For He’s our all in all.{/lang-eng}
